This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Dell Darnell Woods not in court, in custody, appearance waived.  Attorney Michael J Cerniglia appeared by video for Dell Darnell Woods.  Attorney Patrick T. Franken in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in court for Scheduling Conference. Defense has received discovery and an offer from the State and requests a Jury Trial be scheduled. Court sets the deadline of 11/11/2022 for filing of Jury Instructions, Motions in Limine, Witness lists and Change of Plea forms.   State to provide crime lab report prior to the scheduled Final Pretrial Conference.  Case adjourned to Br. 9. Final pre-trial scheduled for November 21, 2022 at 11:00 am. Jury trial scheduled for December 5, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Court orders previous conditions to remain in full force and effect.

Defendant Dell Darnell Woods in court with attorney Michael J Cerniglia appearing via zoom.  Defendant Dell Darnell Woods in custody, produced.  Patrick T. Franken appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Case before this court for Bail hearing.  Defense requests reduction of bail to $2,500.00.  State makes argument.  Court takes judicial notice of Case No. 16CF888 and 21CF4180.  Bail motion by defense is GRANTED by the Court.  Court amends cash bail to $2,500.00. All previous conditions to remain in full force and effect.

Defense has received discovery from the State and requests adjourned Scheduling conference to allow time to review.   Court sets deadline of 8/18/2022 for the State to turnover all discovery including body camera footage. Appropriate sanctions may result for failure to turnover discovery as ordered including exclusion of use of certain discovery as evidence.

Matter adjourned to Br. 9.  Scheduling conference scheduled for August 30, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Dell Darnell Woods in court with Attorney Michael J Cerniglia.  Defendant Dell Darnell Woods in custody.  Abby Rockendorf appeared for the State of Wisconsin. PARTIES APPEAR BY VIDEO.
Court took judicial notice of 16CF888 & 21CF4180. Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: MPD Detective M. Lees. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty. Defense to be heard on bail on the next date. 
*Pursuant to Chief Judge Directive 22-04, parties are hereby notified that effective 7/30/22, this case is assigned to branch 9, Judge Paul Van Grunsven in room 632 of the Courthouse.  Bail/bond hearing scheduled for August 8, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Dell Darnell Woods in court with Attorney Michael J Cerniglia; both appear by video.  Defendant Dell Darnell Woods in custody.  Edward OBrien appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a preliminary hearing. States witness is not present; not working today. Defense doesn't object to an adjournment. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 28, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Dell Darnell Woods in court with attorney Sylvan Jaspen.  Defendant Dell Darnell Woods in custody.  Jack T Eichorst appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Dell Darnell Woods appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Stark, Branch 17.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL. This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 1, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
